## Origin

This rule was first written for the pre-May-2026 world, when `tests/test.sh` was responsible for bootstrapping `curl`, `uv`, and pytest at verifier time. Two variants (A: verbatim V2; B: smart graft with sha256-pinned conditional install) plus a then-emerging Variant C (Dockerfile-baked uv) were the spectrum of accepted shapes.

The May 2026 platform announcement collapsed all three variants into a single rule: every verifier dep is pre-installed in `environment/Dockerfile`, `tests/test.sh` is a thin pytest wrapper, and the runtime sandbox blocks all network calls. The reasoning is straightforward — pre-installation removes the largest source of flakiness in the verifier (transient PyPI / apt failures), and the network block hardens the sandbox against agents that try to exfiltrate or hardcode against external services.

The remaining Doc-06 surface (eager writes + WORKDIR-guard placement) survives the migration unchanged.

A late-May-2026 platform update tightened `tests/test.sh` enforcement further with a literal-text match on the reward-section suffix (the `Must end with the reward section:` message documented in "Static-check suffix requirement" above). The bash-idiomatic `RC=$?` + `if [ "$RC" -eq 0 ]` + trailing `exit "$RC"` shape that `default-template/tests/test.sh` and four in-flight tasks had inherited from older guidance failed this gate; this rule, the default template, the master checklist in `tb2-task-rejection-signals.mdc §11/§15`, the `terminus-project.mdc` canonical example, and the `terminus-task-creator` skill were all updated in the same pass so future tasks ship the conforming literal pattern by construction.
